article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 87, Wagner 72
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Chad Timberlake had 25 points to lead five Fairleigh Dickinson players in double figures and the Knights beat Wagner 87-72 on Saturday. Andrea Crosariol and Gordon Klaiber each added 16 points for the Knights (12-8, 9-2 Northeast Conference), while Andre Harris had 12 and Mike Peoples 10 to go with 10 rebounds. Durelle Vinson had 23 points and 15 rebounds for the Seahawks (10-9, 3-7), while Jamal Smith added 13 points, Mark Porter 12 and James Ulrich 11. Porter made two free throws with 5:59 to play to bring Wagner within 67-62, but Crosariol had six points and Timberlake four in the Knights' 20-10 run to close the game. Crosariol had five points in a 9-0 run that gave FDU a 57-49 lead with 11:58 to go.
